VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'increasingly better. And I highly recommend if you have not heard of Ace Studio or haven\'t really spent any time with it at all to check out at least a couple of the last videos we\'ve done on this platform because since the very first time I reviewed it, it has'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'improved so much in terms of what it will do. Now, if you don\'t know what A Studio is, let me sum it up for you just really briefly. In essence, what A Studio allows you to do is to create highquality vocal tracks without the need for a singer. And there are several'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ways to do this in the platform, many of which I\'ve covered on previous videos and you will get a peek at today. Although today we\'re focusing on a couple of brand new features that make this program even more powerful and fun to work with. Last week we did a video'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'on how to take the songs that you generate in other AI music generation platforms and then replace the AI generated voice with your voice or another voice that you clone. Ace Studio is still another tool that allows you to do this and in a couple of different'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ways. And today one of the new features I\'m going to show you is a new way to input this music data. But let\'s just use this example of replacing a voice in some AI generated song that you did. And Ace makes this drop dead simple and gives you lots of flexibility for'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'remixing as well. The easiest way to do this is just to take an MP3 file and drop it right onto the timeline. This is actually an AI generated song that I\'ve shared on the channel before called Make Out Magic, which I wrote for Tracy for Christmas. So, let\'s just listen to a'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'few seconds of it. [Music] Tracy, I love you. You know that it\'s true. Okay. So now, if we want to change'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'out that voice here in Ace, there\'s a couple of ways we can do it. But the first thing we want to do is to separate these stems and isolate that vocal channel. And we can do that by clicking right here where it says split into'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stems. And we will just go with the default that comes up here and click on split. And we\'ll wait just a few seconds. And then we\'ll have these all split out. Split complete. So here we have the vocal track, the drum track, bass track, and others track. So we\'ll'

[02:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just isolate this vocal track and listen. Tracy, I love you. You know that it\'s true. There are two ways to convert this to another voice. One being infinitely more flexible than the other. And that flexible way is the way that'

